        "description": "Announcement schedule in five-field cron format (minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week). The expression is interpreted in the configured timeZone below, so you can usually enter your local wall-clock schedule directly instead of converting it to UTC by hand. For common routines, pick one of the presets above. Use a custom expression only when you need something more specific. Common examples: */15 * * * * = every 15 minutes, 0 * * * * = at the top of every hour, 30 18 * * 1-5 = 18:30 on weekdays in the selected time zone. Important syntax note: this validator expects plain numbers without zero-padding, so use 5 9 * * 1-5 instead of 05 09 * * 1-5. If validation fails, first remove leading zeros and then double-check each field range. The module polls every minute and only broadcasts on ticks that match this expression in the selected time zone."
      },
      "order": {
        "type": "string",
        "enum": [
          "sequential",
          "random"
